      "text": "A DNS zone is implemented in the configuration system of a [[domain name server]]. Historically, it is defined in the [[zone file]], an operating system [[text file]] that starts with the special DNS record type ''Start of Authority'' (SOA) and contains all records for the resources described within the zone. This format was originally used by the [[BIND]] (BIND) software package, and is defined in RFC 1034 and RFC 1035."
